  "body": "### Describe the feature\n\n## Describe the feature\r\nPlease add support for [Fuse Network](https://fuse.io) Mainnet and Spark testnet chains into hardhat-etherscan.\r\n\r\nFor your reference, [here are the network details](https://docs.fuse.io/docs/basics/getting-started-with-fuse/network-details. Thank you! Love the plugin ðŸš€\r\n\r\nI was able to use the plugin with fuse adding the network as a custom one, now we we would be glad to get the network details included and improve the experience of hardhat on Fuse. Here's the config:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  etherscan: {\r\n    apiKey: {\r\n        fuse: 'mykey'\r\n    },\r\n    customChains: [\r\n      {\r\n        network: \"fuse\",\r\n        chainId: 122,\r\n        urls: {\r\n          apiURL: \"https://explorer.fuse.io/api\",\r\n          browserURL: \"https://explorer.fuse.io\"\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    ]\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
